    "This is where an analysis of the scientific authorship and publication from an autopoietic perspective offers a fruitful perspective on this problem.",
    "The justification for this lies in the humanistic orientation of existing approaches to considering the problem of LLMs in scientific authorship.",
    "Humanistic orientation stresses the importance of human action rather than a more holistic considerations, incorporating other forms of societal realityfor example the scientific system.",
    "This phenomenon is not only about people but also about real abstractions of society.",
    "Moreover, the humanistic approaches often tend to anthropomorphize technical solutions like LLMs (Ji 2024)."
